<TITLE> St Martin's plays host to kite festival </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 29 (bdnews24.com)A daylong kite-flying festival was organised on St Martin's Island Friday. The festival included a seminar on kites and a kite-making workshop. The kite-flying competition started at 10am in front of a tourist resort named "Simana Periye" with a slogan"Fly the Mind's Kite". Chhobir Hat, an organisation of Dhaka University students, organised the festival. Over 100 members of the organisation went to St Martin's Island to attend the programme, first held in 2005. Gias Ahmed, one of the organisers, told bdnews24.com that the festival had been arranged to awaken the "child in every man". "The participants can see the natural beauty of the coral island during the festival. The children of urban areas get the opportunity to fly kites here. This is one of the purposes of coming here," he said. bdnews24.
